<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Randa's Hit Streak Ends at 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Joe Randa's streak of consecutive hits for the  
Kansas City Royals ended at 10 Saturday night, two short of the 
major league record. 
</P>
<P>
	Randa singled in the second inning off Pittsburgh's Jose Silva  
for his team-record 10th hit in 10 at-bats. He then struck out in 
the third, ending his streak. 
</P>
<P>
	Randa fell short of the major league record of 12, shared by  
Pinky Higgins of the 1938 Boston Red Sox and Walt Dropo of the 1952 
Detroit Tigers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Royals' record of eight had been held by several players and  
accomplished most recently by Hall of Famer George Brett in 1980. 
</P>
<P>
	Randa's streak started when he had a two-run single in the  
eighth inning Tuesday against the St. Louis Cardinals. On 
Wednesday, he went 5-for-5 against the Cardinals and then set the 
Royals record by going 3-for-3 with his first two-home run game 
against the Pirates on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	He scored eight runs and drove in eight during the streak.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
