<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-12 16:20:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Show Me the Stage Wins at Calder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Show Me the Stage broke on top and sprinted to a  
3 3/4-length victory Saturday in the $140,000 Azalea Breeders' Cup 
Stakes for 3-year-old fillies at Calder Race Course. 
</P>
<P>
	Could Be was second and Exact was third in a field of nine going  
six furlongs. It was the winner's first start at Calder and her 
seventh stakes victory. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Ricky Courville, Show Me the Stage was timed in 1:11  
4-5 and paid $9.40, $5 and $3.40. Could Be returned $4.40 and $2.80 
and Exact was worth $2.80 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Show Me the Stage has won eight of 15 starts with earnings of  
$247,972. 
</P>
<P>
	The California-bred daughter of Slew the Surgeon posted  
fractions of 21 3-5 for a quarter-mile and 44 flat for a half. 
</P>
<P>
	She opened a two-length lead soon after the start and was three  
lengths in front at the three-eighth pole. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
