<HEADLINE> Wildfires Burn Near Grand Canyon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Wildfires burned hundreds of acres near the Grand Canyon and  
Whiteriver on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire charred 800 acres and sent black smoke 20,000 feet into  
the air. 
</P>
<P>
	Elderly members of the Whiteriver-Apache tribe suffered  
breathing problems and several people were evacuated to a high 
school shelter, though exact numbers weren't available, said Jim 
Anderson of the Apache-Sitgreaves National Forest. 
</P>
<P>
	The fires burned heavy vegetation, trees and brush about 17  
miles south of Pinetop-Lakeside, about 70 miles east of Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
	About 600 acres burned near the north rim of the Grand Canyon  
Friday afternoon from a fire that spread slowly after it was 
sparked by lightning on June 3. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
