<HEADLINE> Quotes From Presidential Hopefuls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Comments from Republican presidential hopefuls during  
campaigning Saturday in Iowa, including a visit on the Iowa State 
Fairgrounds for the World Pork Expo: 

</P>
<P>
	``I think people in Iowa want straight talk. I think they want  
people with the courage of their convictions. That's what I call 
courageous conservatism and that's what I bring to the table.'' -- 
Elizabeth Dole. 

</P>
<P>
	``I haven't seen so much pork since the highway bill passed in  
Congress about a year ago.'' -- U.S. Rep. John Kasich of Ohio. 

</P>
<P>
	``We're raising about $35,000 a day in small donations. I've got  
the best chance to break through.'' -- conservative activist Gary 
Bauer. 

</P>
<P>
	``While Bill Clinton has been diddling and Al Gore has been  
cheerleading, more farmers have been going out of business than 
during the farm crisis of the 1980s.'' -- Former Tennessee Gov. 
Lamar Alexander. 

</P>
<P>
	``The next president, whoever she may be, must stabilize the  
farm economy by exercising leadership to expand domestic markets 
and increase exports.'' -- Mrs. Dole. 

</P>
<P>
	``I hate critiquing everybody else.'' -- Bauer.  

</P>
<P>
	``If Mr. Clinton and Mr. Gore had been chasing foreign markets  
as hard as they have been chasing foreign campaign contributions, 
corn and hog prices would be a lot higher today.'' -- Alexander. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
