<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Student Accused in Deadly Dorm Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- A student rescued by firefighters from a  
burning dormitory last year at Murray State University has been 
charged with setting the blaze, which killed one student and 
injured another. 
</P>
<P>
	Jerry Walker, 23, of Mayfield, was arrested Friday on charges of  
capital murder, first-degree arson and first-degree assault. 
Walker, a senior, is a former member of a campus security unit. 
</P>
<P>
	Commonwealth's Attorney Mike Ward refused to comment on a  
possible motive. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fire was set outside his room. I don't think it was aimed  
at anyone in particular,'' Ward told The Paducah Sun. 
</P>
<P>
	Michael Minger, a 19-year-old student, died in the fire that  
broke out Sept. 18, 1998, at Hester Hall. Michael Priddy, another 
student, was injured. 
</P>
<P>
	Walker was rescued from the window of his dorm room by  
firefighters. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
