<HEADLINE> Murdoch May Buy Publishing Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Rupert Murdoch's New York-based News Corp. is  
in discussions to acquire William Morrow &AMP; Co. and Avon Books, it 
was reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The publishing companies, owned by Hearst Corp., will be added  
to Murdoch's HarperCollins group if the deal is concluded, the 
Hollywood Reporter said. 
