<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  `New' American Solis Rides 4 Winners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Alex Solis, sworn in as an American  
citizen on Thursday, celebrated Friday by riding four winners at 
Hollywood Park, including Aviate in the feature race. 
</P>
<P>
	Solis, a 35-year-old native of Panama, also won with Tanaasa in  
the second race, Bacavi in the fourth and Rock Hound in the fifth 
race. 
</P>
<P>
	Aviate, the 2-5 favorite, took the lead midway through the  
stretch in beating Nausicaa by three lengths in the $51,352 
allowance feature for 3-year-old fillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Aviate, who carried 119 pounds, covered 1 1-16 miles on turf in  
1:41 1-5 and paid $2.80 and $2.10. There was no show betting 
because only four fillies competed. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the third in 10 lifetime starts for Aviate and  
was worth $31,440, increasing the career earnings of the 
Kentucky-bred daughter of Lord Avie to $169,842. 
</P>
<P>
	Nausicaa, ridden by Brice Blanc and carrying 117 pounds, crossed  
the finish line 3 1/2 lengths in front of Courtesan and returned 
$2.40. 
</P>
<P>
	Darlin Echo finished last.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
