<HEADLINE> Marla Maples' Publicist Sentenced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A former publicist for Marla Maples was  
sentenced Friday to 4 1/2 years in prison for burglarizing her 
apartment and taking pajamas, pantyhose and undergarments. 
</P>
<P>
	Chuck Jones, 55, who represented himself, must serve 18 months  
before he is eligible for parole. He was given until Tuesday to 
surrender and was expected to appeal. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones was caught on videotape going through Maples' closets and  
rooms on July 13, 1992, while she was out. Maples, who recently 
agreed to a divorce settlement from Donald Trump, barely remembered 
the items recovered from Jones' office. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones was acquitted of illegal possession of stolen property.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
