<HEADLINE> Running Stag Wins at Belmont </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Running Stag exploded down the stretch for a 7 1/4  
length victory in the 111th running of the $350,000 Brooklyn 
Handicap on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	His time of 1:46:1 tied the fastest in the thirty previous  
runnings of the race at nine furlongs, posted by Formal Gold in 
1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Deputy Diamond was a distant second in the eight horse field  
another 2 1/4 lengths in front of Sir Bear, the favorite. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the first in four starts this year for the  
5-year-old horse. 
</P>
<P>
	Running Stag, ridden by Shane Sellers, earned $210,000 for  
Richard J. Cohen and returned $9.90,$5.60 and $3.20. Deputy Diamond 
paid $6.30 and $3.40 and Sir Bear was $2.40 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
