<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wizards 1, Burn 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Dallas midfielder Chad Deering  
accidentally deflected a shot into his own goal, giving Kansas City 
a 1-0 victory over the Burn on Saturday night, just the second win 
of the season for the Wizards. 
</P>
<P>
	The goal came in the 61st minute, when Wizards forward Chris  
Brown's shot bounced off Burn goalkeeper Matt Jordan to Deering, 
who deflected it into the goal. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas managed just nine total shots, three on goal. Kansas City  
(2-10) attempted 18 shots, eight on goal. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first loss in regulation for Dallas (7-5), which is  
2-5 away from the Cotton Bowl, where they will play Eastern 
Conference leader D.C. United on Wednesday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
